The court is meant to deal with suspected corruption and white-collar financial crimes and dispose them speedily in view of recovering plundered resources. The court has been established in line with President Hakainde Hichilema's vision to fight graft. Meanwhile Zambia's Kitwe and District Chamber of Commerce and Industry has advised the Mine Workers Union of Zambia to prepare adequately for challenges it may face once it begins to run its own mine. The Unions President Joseph Chewe announced that the union is currently working on opening and operating its own mine and is looking at North Western, Central and Luapula Provinces to Set Up. Chamber Vice President In-Charge of Commerce Emmanuel Mbambiko has meanwhile wondered to what extent the union will exercise control over its human resource costs related to its members turned into employees at the mine while remaining profitable. --ChannelAfrica---